	location = {New York, {NY}, {US}},
	title = {Behavioral expressions and biosocial bases of sensation seeking},
	isbn = {978-0-521-43200-9 978-0-521-43770-7},
	series = {Behavioral expressions and biosocial bases of sensation seeking},
	abstract = {[This] book describes the research and theory on sensation seeking with emphasis on the new findings since [1979]. The behavioral expressions of sensation seeking have been found in various kinds of risk-taking behaviors such as driving habits, health, gambling, financial activities, alcohol and drug use, sexual behavior, and sports. The trait is also involved in vocational preferences and choices, job satisfaction, social premarital and marital relationships, eating habits and food preferences, media and art preferences, humor, fantasy, creativity, and social attitudes. Its modes of assessment, behavioral expressions, and genetic and psychobiological bases are described by [Marvin Zuckerman]. In the last chapter the author develops a biosocial model for the trait.  This book [will interest] researchers and their students active in personality research. ({PsycINFO} Database Record (c) 2016 {APA}, all rights reserved)},
